{
  "stem": "26765.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And after the Germans invaded and conquered Holland, they replaced the people who were in office, the Dutch mayor, the Dutch governors, with their own people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so they put a Nazi mayor in that little town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that Nazi mayor, of course, knew that there were Jewish children hidden at the convent.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In 1941, already, the nuns, the Mother Superior, Sister Renaldas, who was an exceptionally brave woman-- and she, together with the rector, received notice that they had to hand over Annamarie and Evi Goldberg.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were placed in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they died Auschwitz, already in 1941.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The following year, the third-- all Jewish girl-- Ilse Brul-- Ilse was a girl who was very proud to be Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I don't think that-- she wasn't discriminated against because she wanted to be Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know, remember, most of the children there were Catholic, because they were half Catholic.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We were baptized.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But she was 16, 17 at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And she said, no, I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I want to remain Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That is my heritage.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That is the religion of my parents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she was a very unusual girl.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And she made a tremendous impression on me, even though she was not one of the girls that played with me a lot, because she kind of kept to herself.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "She was somewhat reserved.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But she had a presence and a security about her that impressed me as a child.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Well, in 1942, the officers came to the convent.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they-- it was time for Ilse to be sent to a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And Ilse was sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "On the train, she wrote a letter to the Mother Superior of the convent, thanking her.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
